### Infrastructure Task Format

```json
{
  "id": "task-001",
  "title": "Provision Application Infrastructure",
  "description": "Deploy all infrastructure: PostgreSQL (CloudNative-PG), Redis, Kafka (Strimzi), MongoDB (Percona), SeaweedFS S3",
  "priority": "critical",
  "dependencies": [],
  "agentHint": "bolt",
  "details": "Infrastructure from PRD:\n\n1. PostgreSQL (CloudNative-PG):\n   - Cluster name: alerthub-db\n   - Instances: 2 (primary + replica)\n   - Storage: 20Gi on mayastor\n   - Connection pooler enabled\n   - Secret: alerthub-db-secret\n\n2. Redis (Valkey):\n   - Name: alerthub-cache\n   - Mode: standalone with persistence\n   - Memory: 512Mi\n   - Secret: alerthub-cache-secret\n\n3. Kafka (Strimzi):\n   - Cluster: alerthub-kafka\n   - Topics: notifications, events, dlq\n   - Partitions: 3 per topic\n   - Replication: 2\n\n4. Create ConfigMap alerthub-infra-config with all connection strings",
  "testStrategy": "1. kubectl get cluster alerthub-db -n alerthub → Status: READY, Instances: 2/2\n2. kubectl exec -it alerthub-db-1 -- psql -c 'SELECT 1' → Returns 1\n3. kubectl get redis alerthub-cache → READY\n4. redis-cli -h alerthub-cache PING → PONG\n5. kubectl get kafka alerthub-kafka → Ready: True\n6. kubectl get kafkatopic → notifications, events, dlq exist\n7. ConfigMap alerthub-infra-config contains: POSTGRES_URL, REDIS_URL, KAFKA_BROKERS"
}
