## Context Embedding Strategy

For each task, embed relevant PRD sections in `details`:

### Backend API Tasks (Rex/Grizz/Nova)

```json
{
  "details": "From PRD Section: Notification Router Service\n\nEndpoints to implement:\n- POST /api/v1/notifications - Submit notification\n  - Request: { tenant_id, channel, priority, payload }\n  - Response: { id, status, created_at }\n  - Validation: tenant_id required, channel in [slack, discord, email, push]\n\n- GET /api/v1/notifications/:id - Get status\n  - Response: { id, status, events: [...] }\n\nData Model (from PRD):\n```rust\nstruct Notification {\n    id: Uuid,\n    tenant_id: Uuid,\n    channel: Channel,\n    priority: Priority,\n    payload: NotificationPayload,\n    status: NotificationStatus,\n}\n```\n\nDependencies: PostgreSQL (alerthub-db), Redis (alerthub-cache)\nConnection strings in ConfigMap: alerthub-infra-config",
  "testStrategy": "1. POST /api/v1/notifications returns 201 with notification ID\n2. Invalid tenant_id returns 400\n3. GET /api/v1/notifications/:id returns notification with events\n4. cargo test --all passes\n5. cargo clippy -- -D warnings passes\n6. Integration test: create notification → verify in PostgreSQL → check Redis dedup key"
}
```

### Frontend Tasks (Blaze/Tap/Spark)

```json
{
  "details": "From PRD Section: Web Dashboard\n\nPages to implement:\n1. /notifications - List view with filters\n   - Filter by: status, channel, date range\n   - Pagination: 20 per page\n   - Real-time updates via WebSocket\n\n2. /notifications/:id - Detail view\n   - Show: payload, delivery events timeline, retry button\n\nUI Components needed:\n- NotificationList (with virtual scrolling)\n- NotificationCard (status badge, channel icon)\n- FilterBar (dropdown + date picker)\n- DeliveryTimeline (event visualization)\n\nAPI Integration:\n- GET /api/v1/notifications?status=X&channel=Y&page=N\n- WS /api/v1/ws for real-time updates\n\nUse shadcn/ui components: Card, Badge, Select, DatePicker, ScrollArea",
  "testStrategy": "1. npm run build succeeds without errors\n2. npm run lint passes\n3. /notifications renders list from API\n4. Filters update URL params and refresh data\n5. WebSocket connects and updates list in real-time\n6. playwright test: filter by status → verify correct items shown"
}
```

